-- Nokia and Intuit Start India Pilot of Small Business SMS Service
-- B y   D i a n a   b e n - A a r o n
-- 2010-11-23T10:58:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/nokia-intuit-start-indian-pilot-of-ad-sms-service-for-small-businesses.html
Nokia Oyj and Intuit Inc. are
running a pilot in India of a service to help small business
owners send ads and personalized messages to their customers via
mobile phone and Web.  The service, called Intuit GoConnect, is available from
today in New Delhi and Chandigarh, Nokia said in a statement.
Prices start at 2400 rupees ($52.64) for 10,000 text messages
over six months. A national Indian launch is planned for early
2011, spokesman Mark Durrant said by e-mail.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Diana Ben-Aaron at 
 dbenaaron1@bloomberg.net  